<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7995> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7995" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 145. -Procos. in Hisp. Ult. 144 (MRR 1.471). Refer also to Diod. 33.7.5-7.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7995 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6985> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6985" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the succession of embassies from 156 to 154 caused by the hostilities between Prusias II of Bithynia and Attalus lI of Pergamum, see Chr. Habicht (Hermes 84, 1956, 90-116, and RE s. v. Prusias II), whose reordering of the relevant fragments of Polybius has been accepted by Walbank (Comm. Polyb. III, on 32.16.1; 33.1; 32.15.1-4; 33.7, 12.1-13.10, with references to earlier discussions on p. 540). See MRR 1.448-451. The attack on Attalus in 156 caused Lentulus to return to Rome with the Attalid prince Athenaeus, but before their arrival a doubting Senate had sent L. Appuleius and C. Petronius. The report of Lentulus and Athenaeus led to the immediate appointment, probably late in 156, of a new embassy, C. Claudius Centho, L. Hortensius and C. Aurunculeius, who reached Pergamum in the spring of 155 in time to arrange a conference which was ruined by Pharnaces' treachery, to be immured in Pergamum and to see the havoc Pharnaces caused. By autumn they had returned to Rome, and a commission of ten was sent, led by L. Anicius Gallus, C. Fannius Strabo, and Q. Fabius Maximus Aemilianus, late in 155 or early in 154, who observed Attalus' victorious counterattack and returned. Finally, in summer 154, a new embassy, Ap. Claudius Centho, L. Oppius, and A. Postumius Albinus, secured peace between the two kings, and the payment of indemnities by Prusias to Attalus and the Greek cities. See also L. Robert, Et. Anat. 110-115." ;
	dprr:hasID 6985 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3144> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3144" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served in Spain with his brother Scipio (App. Ib. 90)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3144 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3017> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3017" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His command in Farther Spain was prorogued at Scipio's suggestion (Val. Max. 6.4.2). His army now trained, he won some successes against Viriathus and wintered at Corduba (App. Ib. 65; cf. Cic. Rab. Post. 2; Vell. 2.5.3)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3017 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3005> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3005" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Lael. 96; Liv. Oxy. Per. 52; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 124, 466f. (Q. Fabius [Q. f. Q. n. Max.] Aimilianus, L. Hostilius L. [f.] L. n. Mancinus); Fast. Ant., ib. 160f. ([- - - -Ma]x., L. Hostili. Man.); Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Hostilius, Plin. NH 35.23. Fabius brought a new army to Farther Spain, and during the training period suffered a minor reverse at the hands of Viriathus while absent at Gades (App. Ib. 65; cf. Liv. Oxy. Per. 52; Flor. 1.33.17; see Schulten, NJ 39 [1917] 221)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3005 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2938> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2938" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Received the Carthaginian hostages and conveyed them to Rome (Polyb. 36.5.8-9)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2938 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2893> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2893" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent with seven others stop the war between Prusias and Attalus when the previous embassy failed (see 155, Legates, no. a). Upon Prusias' refusal to withdraw they ordered Attalus to protect his kingdom, and separated, some to report to the Senate, some to break up Prusias' alliances (Polyb. 33.7.1-4, and 12-13.4; cf. App. Mith. 3)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2893 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2798> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2798" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent with Scipio Nasica (see Tribunes of the Soldiers) to raid Illyria and bring the army to Oricum (Liv. 45.33.8, and 34.8). See 168, Legates." ;
	dprr:hasID 2798 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2763> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2763" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Paullus, and volunteered with Scipio Nasica to carry out the flanking march which drove Perseus' army back to Pydna (Liv. 44.35.14-23; cf. Polyb. 29.14.1-3; Plut. Aem. 15.3-6)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2763 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2753> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2753" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to Rome by Paullus to report his victory at Pydna (Liv. 44.45.3; 45.1-2)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2753 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10072> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10072" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/31> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph? de Lusitaneis. Itgenshorst no.212a (triumphus incertus, 143?). Not listed in MRR or Rich." ;
	dprr:hasID 10072 .
